content:
To add a sidebar with the navlinks home, about, and contact, you can use HTML and CSS code. Here is an example:

HTML code:
```
<div class="sidebar">
  <ul>
    <li><a href="/">Home</a></li>
    <li><a href="/about">About</a></li>
    <li><a href="/contact">Contact</a></li>
  </ul>
</div>
```

CSS code:
```
.sidebar {
  background-color: #f2f2f2;
  padding: 20px;
  width: 200px;
  height: 100%;
  position: fixed;
  top: 0;
  left: 0;
}

.sidebar ul {
  list-style: none;
  margin: 0;
  padding: 0;
}

.sidebar li {
  margin-bottom: 10px;
}

.sidebar a {
  text-decoration: none;
  color: #333;
  font-weight: bold;
}

.sidebar a:hover {
  color: #666;
}
```

You can customize the styles according to your preferences. Remember to link this code to your HTML document.
